ports that were made such as Mortal Kombat II and Super Street Fighter II. I think you would agree for the SNES these were both very well received ports despite not being close to 1:1 with the arcade original. While the subject of if a perfect or better port is possible is interesting I think it is ultimately futile sense SNK is not interested in producing a new SNES port and I don't believe anyone is interested in reverse engineering a NeoGeo game to then port it to SNES. If they were that would be very cool. </div>
<br />
<br />Ports 1:1 are obviously not possible (as I said before...) because of colors, resolution and a different video sub-system, but maybe they could have achieved more accurate results if time and ROM weren't so important. I don't say that programmers were lazy, but you can't compare what last SNES games could do (like DKC3) with the first ones did...
<br />There is no point in repeating what <strong>tokumaru</strong> said, I agree 100% with him...

		

